response: Ali Addeh refugee camp in Djibouti is home to 10,000 Eritrean refugees. Many have been waiting years for resettlement through the UN. Some are turning to smugglers due to a lack of progress. The Eritrean government is brutal and many refugees are forced to flee.
answer:
For 25 years, Ali Addeh refugee camp has been a holding point for those fleeing into Djibouti .
Many come from Somalia, Ethiopia and especially Eritrea -- which is ruled by a one-party state .
Despite the risks, Eritrean refugees say they'd risk their lives with people smugglers .

Dennis Hutchings, a 73-year-old former soldier, has been charged with attempted murder in connection with the death of John Pat Cunningham in 1974.
Cunningham was a mentally disabled man shot and killed by the British Army in Northern Ireland. 
Hutchings has been released on bail and is scheduled for a court appearance in June. 
The case has been reopened by the PSNI and is being investigated.
Cunningham's family has asked for an independent investigation.
answer:
John Pat Cunningham, 27, was shot dead by the Army in a field in 1974 .
British government later apologised and investigation re-opened this year .
Dennis Hutchings appeared in court today and was released on bail .
He was arrested in England and taken to Northern Ireland for questioning .

UEFA rules that England's U19 women's qualifier against Norway must be replayed after a refereeing mistake. The replay will be played on Thursday at 9:45pm. The match will resume with England retaking a penalty in the 96th minute. 

**Note:** This is a summary of the article and may not contain all the details.
answer:
UEFA have ordered the final 18 seconds of the qualifier to be replayed .
England will resume the match against Norway from the penalty spot .
The Elite Round qualifier resumes in Belfast on Thursday at 9:45pm .
Referee Marija Kurtes incorrectly awarded an indirect free-kick to Norway for encroachment after disallowing England's penalty on Saturday .
England were 2-1 down to Norway at the time in the 96th minute .
German Kurtes, 28, has been sent home following her error .
Three Lions earn 3-1 victory against Switzerland meaning a 2-2 will be enough for European Championship qualification .
Norway beat Northern Ireland 8-1 to keep things tight in Group 4 .
It is the first time ever that a decision like this has been taken by UEFA .

response: Fake photos and videos from Sydney's devastating storm emerge. Images include a trampoline in power lines, a crocodile in a train station, and a wave rider surfing in front of the Opera House.
answer:
In the midst of the worst storm in New South Wales in a decade people got creative with their Photoshopping skills .
While there were many genuine dramatic photos of the devastation caused, the fake ones also caused confusion .
The more unbelievable Photoshop jobs included a photo of Noah's ark majestically cruising into Sydney Harbour .
